@startuml RunnersHi_RunnersHi_Server

actor Client
participant "Express Server" as Server
participant "Socket.IO" as SocketIO
participant "Auth Middleware" as AuthMiddleware
participant "Controllers" as Controllers
participant "Models" as Models
database "MySQL Database" as DB

Client -> Server: HTTP Request
Server -> AuthMiddleware: Authenticate request
AuthMiddleware -> Models: Verify token
Models -> DB: Query user data
DB --> Models: Return user data
Models --> AuthMiddleware: Token validity
AuthMiddleware --> Server: Authentication result

alt Authentication Successful
    Server -> Controllers: Route to appropriate controller
    Controllers -> Models: Request data
    Models -> DB: Query database
    DB --> Models: Return data
    Models --> Controllers: Processed data
    Controllers --> Server: Response data
    Server --> Client: HTTP Response
else Authentication Failed
    AuthMiddleware --> Server: Authentication error
    Server --> Client: 401 Unauthorized
end

Client -> SocketIO: Connect for real-time updates
SocketIO -> Controllers: Handle socket event
Controllers -> Models: Update/Retrieve data
Models -> DB: Perform database operation
DB --> Models: Operation result
Models --> Controllers: Updated data
Controllers --> SocketIO: Emit event with data
SocketIO --> Client: Real-time update

@enduml